{"key":"processedPost-8491975","value":{"id":8491975,"first":8491818,"last":8492040,"when":1212763814,"utime":"06/06/08 05:50 PM","cleanedPost":"Quite frankly, with dunking, I see little benefit to a casing layer on manure, coir, compost or straw, as long as <i>P cubensis</i> is all you're growing.<br />Mist as required right through harvest.&nbsp; Misting doesn't cause aborts.&nbsp; Primordia and small pins get baptised by thunderstorms in texas and florida that literally dump buckets of water on them and they don't abort.&nbsp; Misting, and then sealing up in an improperly-built fruiting chamber with no air exchange will definitely cause aborts.<br />Fan well after each misting and you'll be fine.<br />RR"}}